        "text": "Director Roland Emmerich vows that he’s had it with disaster pictures, but if that’s the case, he’s going out with a bang. The man behind Independence Day and The Day After Tomorrow has assembled a cavalcade of special-effects catastrophes for 2012, which features John Cusack (pictured) as a family man reacting to a doomsday scenario predicted by the Mayan calendar\n\nSee also: Wes Anderson Directs Fantastic Mr. Fox From Afar\n\nReview: Military Dudes Abide in Funny Men Who Stare at Goats\n\nReview: Gentlemen Broncos Rides Sci-Fi Cheese Into Ground</p>\n\nAopening Friday in limited release is <em>astic Mr. Fox</emorge Clooney follows last week’s mind-over-matter comedy <em>*Men Who Stare at Goats</a>h the title voice role in this adaptation of Roald Dahl’s fable.</p>\n\nDctor Wes Anderson (<em>*Royal Tenenbaums</a>ed the internet to orchestrate the stop-motion British production from his Paris home and still managed to hammer his meticulously detailed art direction into place for the cinematic adaptation of the children’s tale.</p>\n\nAtional weekend openings include <em>te Radio</ematuring Philip Seymour Hoffman as a renegade disc jockey who defies a British government ban by broadcasting rock music from an offshore ship.</p>\n\nRing out in expanded release is the Sundance-winning drama <em>ious</emich details the harsh life of an illiterate Harlem mother (played by newcomer <a hurey Sidibe</a>p>\n\nRmore about this week’s theatrical offerings and watch trailers below.</p>\n\ning This Week</h2\n\nmbed: /video/2012-movie-trailer/iframe?videoId=5171b42fc2b4c00dd0c20082&autoplay=false&muted=0&adsDisabled=0&iu=3379/conde.wired/legacy] <p> >\n\nr_</a>_> rpsis:</stDecember 2012, a pending cataclysm — caused by the Earth’s core being boiled by mutant neutrinos — prompts the government to prepare Chinese ships for the preservation of the species. Jackson Curtis (played by <a h Cusack</a>eparated from his wife (Amanda Peet), braves earthquakes, tsunamis, volcanoes and the implosion of cultural landmarks and cities to save his family. Chiwetel Ejiofor, Thandie Newton, Oliver Platt, Woody Harrelson and Danny Glover co-star for director Roland Emmerich (<em>pendence Day</emm>Day After Tomorrow</emr> rd:</st13</p>\n\nsure:</sthrich Rewrites History, the Future (After Destroying Earth)</a>rure:</sth2 ‘s Doomsday Predecessors: An Apocalyptic Primer</a>\n\nr_te Radio</a>_> rpsis:</stt-based comedy recounts the story of deejays who, after being banned from the British airways in the 1960s, broadcast music by The Who, The Kinks, Jimi Hendrix and Cream from an old tanker in the North Sea. Philip Seymour Hoffman heads the cast, which also features Bill Nighy, Rhys Ifans, Nick Frost and Kenneth Branagh. Richard Curtis’ (<em> Weddings and a Funeral</emrects.<br> rd:</stp>\n\nr_astic Mr. Fox</a>_> rpsis:</stp-motion fable features the wily Mr. Fox (voiced by George Clooney) as a wily predator surrounded by the cautious Mrs. Fox (Meryl Streep) and depressed son Ash (Jason Schwartzman). Rat, badgers and evil farmers round out the story, with additional voices provided by Bill Murray, Adrien Brody, Owen Wilson, Willem Dafoe and Michael Gambon. Wes Anderson (<em>Life Aquatic</emrects.<br> rd:</st/p>\n\nsure:</sthAnderson Directs Fantastic Mr. Fox From Afar</a>\n\nr_ious</a>panding)</em_> rpsis:</st in Harlem in 1987, the story centers on 16-year-old illiterate Precious Jones (first-time actress Gabourey Sidibe). Browbeaten and physically abused by her mother, Mo’Nique, she becomes pregnant with her second child and pursues an alternative school. Based on the novel <em></emSapphire, <em>ious</emrected by Lee Daniels (<em>Woodsman</emo-stars Mariah Carey and Paula Patton.<br> rd:</stp>\n\nheaters Now</h2\n\nmbed: /video/a-christmas-carol-in-3d/iframe?videoId=5171b442c2b4c00dd0c204f9&autoplay=false&muted=0&adsDisabled=0&iu=3379/conde.wired/legacy] <p> >\n\nr_ristmas Carol</a>_> rpsis:</stert Zemeckis (<em> to the Future, The Polar Express</emd his ImageMovers Digital team put a 3-D, motion-capture spin on Charles Dickens’ oft-told tale of redemption. Jim Carrey (<em>ured above</emays the misanthropic Scrooge, who learns life lessons from Tiny Tim and kindly wage-slave Bob Cratchit (both voiced by <a h Oldman</a>olin Firth, Bob Hoskins and Robin Wright Penn co-star.<br> rd:</st/p>\n\nsure:</sthpy, Cool Ghosts of <em>stmas Carols</emt</a>\n\nr_Men Who Stare at Goats</a>_> rpsis:</strge Clooney stars as ex-Special Forces spy Lyn Cassady, who developed his psychic abilities in the 1980s. Teaming with journalist Bob Wilton (<a h McGregor</a> present-day Iraq, Cassady hits the road on a kooky mission. Based on Jon Ronson’s 2004 book, the movie co-stars Jeff Bridges and Kevin Spacey. Grant Heslov (<em> Night and Good Luck</emrects.<br> rd:</stp>\n\nsew:</sthtary Dudes Abide in Funny Men Who Stare at Goats </a>rure:</sthhic Spies, Acid Guinea Pigs, New Age Soldiers: the True Men Who Stare at Goats </a>rer Room review:</sthMovie Can’t Top Real-Life Men Who Stare at Goats </a>\n\nr_Fourth Kind</a>_> rpsis:</st-fi thriller delves into unexplained disappearances in Nome, Alaska, supposedly uncovered nine years ago by a sleep-disorder researcher (<em>dent Evil</emilla Jovovich). Under hypnosis, her subjects experience visions of murder, suicide and demonic possession pegged to alien mind control. <a hunde Osunsanmi</a>ects.<br> rd:</stp>\n\nr_Box</a>_> rpsis:</steron Diaz and James Marsden play struggling suburban parents who find a wooden box on their doorstep. Soon afterward, a disfigured stranger (<a hk Langella</a>fers the couple $1 million to press a button on the box causing the death of another human being somewhere in the world. Writer-director Richard Kelly (<em>ie Darko</emapts the short story by Richard Matheson.<br> rd:</st13</p>\n\nmbed: /video/gentlemen-broncos-trailer/iframe?videoId=5171b442c2b4c00dd0c204db&autoplay=false&muted=0&adsDisabled=0&iu=3379/conde.wired/legacy] <p> >\n\nr_lemen Broncos</a>_> rpsis:</stn teen sci-fi fan Benjamin (played by <a hael Angarano</a>tends a writer’s camp, his story “Yeast Lords” gets seen by famed author Ronald Chevalier (Jemaine Clement, TV’s <em>ht of the Conchords</emctured above with Angarano) and later becomes an awful movie featuring “Bronco” (<a hRockwell</a>m></emennifer Coolidge co-stars for co-writer/director Jared Hess (<em>leon Dynamite</emr> rd:</st13</p>\n\nsew:</sthtlemen Broncos Rides Sci-Fi Cheese Into Ground</a>\n\nr Is It</a>> rpsis:</st posthumous tribute follows Michael Jackson as he rehearses for a series of sold-out shows in London. The music documentary is directed by Jackson’s choreographer, Kenny Ortega.<br> rd:</st/p>\n\nr_House of the Devil</a>_> rpsis:</ster a college co-ed (Jocelin Donahue) gets a babysitting gig at a Victorian mansion deep in the woods, she encounters a lunar eclipse and an unwholesome stranger. Greta Gerwig (<em>ead</emom Noonan (<em> Angels</emary Woronov and Dee Wallace (<em></em-star. Ti West directs.<br> rd:</stp>\n\nr***Boondock Saints II: All Saints Day</a>mited)</st**> rpsis:</stter-director Troy Duffy’s action sequel tracks the vigilante MacManus brothers (Norman Reedus and Sean Patrick Flanery), who return from exile in Ireland to avenge the death of a priest in Boston. The cast also includes Julie Benz (TV’s <em>er</emilly Connolly and Clifton Collins Jr. (<em> Trek</emr> rd:</stp>\n\nmbed: /video/astro-boy-trailer/iframe?videoId=5171b433c2b4c00dd0c20190&autoplay=false&muted=0&adsDisabled=0&iu=3379/conde.wired/legacy] <p> >\n\nr_o Boy</a>_> rpsis:</st in futuristic Metro City, Toby (aka Astro Boy, pictured above) comes to life after Dr. Tenma (voiced by Nicolas Cage) endows the robot hero with X-ray vision, speed and the ability to fly. Astro Boy fights corruption but faces disappointment upon learning that he’s not human. Additional voices include Kristen Bell, Charlize Theron and Samuel L. Jackson. Director David Bowers (<em>k Tale</emses this adaptation on Osamu Tezuka’s 1951 Japanese manga and subsequent anime series.<br> rd:</st/p>\n\nsery:</stho Boy Gets the Hollywood-Blockbuster Treatment</a>rure:</stht Look: <em>o Boy</emisten Bell Plug Into Comic-Con</a>ro:</sthten Bell on Robot Emotion in <em>o Boy</em\n\nr_ia</a>_> rpsis:</stiod drama features <a hry Swank</a>m>ion Dollar Baby</em aviation pioneer Amelia Earhart. The film chronicle’s Earhart’s Depression-era adventures prior to 1937 disappearance over the Pacific during an attempted round-the-world flight. Richard Gere and Ewan McGregor co-star for director Mira Nair (<em>oon Wedding</emr> rd:</st/p>\n\nr_VI</a>_> rpsis:</st torturous reign of terror wrought by the Jigsaw Killer (<a hn Bell)</a>tinues as FBI Agent Hoffman (<a has Mandylor</a>ies to stop the madness.<br> rd:</st13</p>\n\nr_ue du Freak: The Vampire’s Assistant</a>_> rpsis:</sth C. Reilly</a>rs as a vampire who mentors a teenager (Chris Massoglia) en route to a traveling freak show. Paul Weitz (<em>t a Boy, American Pie</emrects.<br> rd:</st13</p>\n\nr***christ</a>mited)</st**> rpsis:</sthem Dafoe</a>m>er-Man</emd <a hlotte Gainsbourg</a>m>Science of Sleep</emar as a married couple who deal with a personal tragedy in a forest hideaway. Lars von Trier directs.<br> rd:</st rated</p>\n\ns**-review:</streat deceiver, Antichrist shows initial promise as an exercise in art-house horror: Beautiful, slow-motion imagery set to an operatic soundtrack introduces a wildly copulating couple and reveals the incident that will drive their story of sex and sadness. After their loss, He (Willem Dafoe), a therapist, retreats with his grieving wife, She (Charlotte Gainsbourg), to a cabin in the woods. But once in “Satan’s church,” psychobabble gives way to occult mumbo jumbo, genital mutilation and surreal woodland creatures as the movie deteriorates into a mess of confused symbolism. Perhaps it makes sense on some level — one can imagine a dope-smoking student banging out a thesis about the film’s deep connections — but on the face of it, Danish director <a h Von Trier</a> cooked up a hellish drama that is visually compelling, <a huently laughable</a> ultimately disappointing. <em>wis Wallace</emrng:</st**\n\nmbed: /video/where-the-wild-things-are-movie-trailer/iframe?videoId=5171b43ec2b4c00dd0c203fd&autoplay=false&muted=0&adsDisabled=0&iu=3379/conde.wired/legacy] <p> >\n\nr_e the Wild Things Are</a>_> rpsis:</stappy at home, Max (played by <a hRecords</a>capes to an island inhabited by unpredictable Wild Things. There, Max rises to power before becoming entangled in nature’s rough-and-tumble realities. Catherine Keener and Mark Ruffalo star as humans. The costumed creatures are voiced by James Gandolfini, Paul Dano, Forest Whitaker and Lauren Ambrose. Adapted from Maurice Sendak’s classic children’s picture book by director Spike Jonze (<em>g John Malkovich</emd co-scripter <a h Eggers</a>m>artbreaking Work of Staggering Genius</emhe film features a soundtrack by electronic music pioneer Carter Burwell and the Yeah Yeah Yeahs’ Karen O. Tom Hanks produces.<br> rd:</st/p>\n\nsew:</sthre the Wild Things Are Is Woolly, But Not Wild Enough</a>ro:</sthak Says <em> Things</emm as Feral as Book</a>rure:</sthe Jones Melds F/X and Muppetry for <em> Things</em\n\nr_Abiding Citizen</a>_> rpsis:</stde Shelton (<a hrd Butler</a>es his wife and daughter killed in a home-invasion robbery, then methodically seeks revenge after prosecutor Nick Rice (<a he Foxx</a>rikes a deal with the perpetrators. F. Gary Grey (<em>Italian Job</emrects.<br> rd:</stp>\n\nr***Stepfather</a>mited)</st**> rpsis:</stake of the 1987 horror movie features Dylan Walsh (<em>Tuck</em a stepfather who might be a lot more dangerous than he seems. Sela Ward co-stars.<br> rd:</st13</p>\n\nr_les Retreat</a>_> rpsis:</st>gers</emm Jon Favreau and Vince Vaughn play a couple of Midwestern guys who join their wives and two other couples at a tropical island resort. The twist: Therapy sessions are part of the program. Directed by actor <a hr Billingsley</a>m>Sacred Fire</emhe domestic comedy co-stars Malin Ackerman, Jason Bateman, Kristin Davis, Kristen Bell and Faizon Love.<br> rd:</st13</p>\n\nr_normal Activity</a>_> rpsis:</stuburban couple becomes increasingly freaked out when spooky phenomena captured on home security cameras suggests that their bedroom is co-occupied by demons. Writer-director Oren Peli made the film on an $11,000 budget. Cast includes Katie Featherston, Micah Sloat, Mark Fredrichs, Amber Armstrong and Ashley Palmer.<br> rd:</stp>\n\nsew:</sthBudget <em>normal Activity</emills With High-Value Horror</a>\n\nmbed: /post/movies-2012/iframe?videoId=5171b430c2b4c00dd0c200be&autoplay=false&muted=0&adsDisabled=0&iu=3379/conde.wired/legacy] <p> >\n\nr_ieland</a>_> rpsis:</stward teen Columbus (played by Jesse Eisenberg) survives a zombie plague and teams up with fellow Twinkie-loving badass Tallahassee (Woody Harrelson) on a bloody cross-country trip culminating in an amusement park showdown. Bill Murray, Abigail Breslin and Emma Stone co-star for director <a hn Fleischer</a>’s <em>y Kimmel Live</emr> rd:</stp>\n\nsure:</sthng <em>ieland</emwesome Ghoul-Killing Weapons</a>\n\nr_Invention of Lying</a>_> rpsis:</strring co-writer/co-director Ricky Gervais, the story takes place in an alternative universe that resembles normal society in every regard except that nobody lies. When a down-on-his-luck loser (Gervais) stumbles upon a way to lie, he uses his newfound ability to woo the ladies. Jennifer Garner, Jonah Hill, Louis C.K., Rob Lowe and Tina Fey co-star.<br> rd:</st13</p>\n\nr_dy With a Chance of Meatballs</a>_> rpsis:</stad scientist out to solve world hunger sees his experiment go awry when food that’s programmed into his latest invention starts falling from the sky. The animated 3-D comedy, based on Judi and Ron Barrett’s best-selling novel, is directed by Phil Lord (TV’s <em>e High</emd animation artist Chris Miller (<em>k</emm>gascar</emth voice work by Bill Hader, Anna 